      It was pretty much exactly how I predicted. I don't quite know how Hart is in the team when Forster is twice the keeper. I didn't expect either team to play "well", it's a derby and I hardly ever see derbies consist of great football where both teams genuinely want to win. It's just about grinding out a result somehow and that we did. I expect Vardy and Sturridge to start with Lallana in a front 3 against Slovakia given Sterling and Kane have now put in 2 poor performances. Wales will have too much for Russia. They defended in the same way Atletico Madrid do, as one. You can't really teach that. Players either buy your philosophy or you get sacked.
